							<h2 class="page-header" style="text-align:center">Explanations for 2004 -2014 Significant Losses and Pattern Templates</h2>
						</div>
							<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This dataset comprises a Drawdown dataset of individual equities that are included in the S&P 500 Index. 
								We consider data from 2004 to 2014. A (monthly) Drawdown represents the day where the equity experiences the 
								lowest price for that month. The Drawdown data was corrected (CAPM_resid Drawdown); the correction included a
								factor that is based on the correlation of the equity price with the S&P 500 index historically.</p>
						   
						    <p>We use the Top 10++% Significant Losses for our analysis. This is determined as a UNION of the Top 10% Drawdown
						     values and the Top 10% Loss of market capitalization values.</p>
						    <p>Market capitalization = Price * Count_of_Outstanding_Shares for the individual equity</p>
						    <h5>Consider the following chart with Blue and Orange and Red and Green bars:</h5>
						    <center><img style="max-width:600px;"" src="bootstrap/img/definitions.jpg"></center>
						    
						    <ul>
						    	<li><b>Blue: </b> &nbsp;&emsp;Cumulative loss of market capitalization using most significant CAPM_resid drawdown individual equities.</li>
						    	<li><b>Orange:</b>&nbsp;S&P 500 Index drawdown.</li>
						    	<li><b>Red:</b>&emsp;&emsp;End_of_month Loss of market capitalization for blue equities.</li>
						    	<li><b>Green:</b>&emsp;End_of_month S&P 500 Index Market capitalization.</li>
						    </ul>
						    <br>
						    <p><b>SMALL and LARGE market capitalization threshold was calculated using the yearly range of values of market capitalization.</b></p>
						    <img src="bootstrap/img/scale.png">
						    <p>Based on the values of the blue, orange, red and green bars we identified the following four templates or patterns: <b>PUSHDOWN / LOSS NO IMPACT / NO IMPACT / NON ALIGN</b>
						    </p>
						    
						    <ul>
						    	<li><b>PUSHDOWN</b> Blue bar is LARGE NEGATIVE. Red bar is negative. Green bar is LARGE NEGATIVE. The Blue loss of market capitalization did not fully recover by the end of the month (red is negative) and this pushed down the index.</li><br>
						    	
						    	<li><b>LOSS NO IMPACT: HIGH LOSS LOW GAIN</b> Blue bar is LARGE NEGATIVE. Red bar is small negative or small positive. Green bar is close to zero or small positive.</li><br>
						    	<li><b>NO IMPACT: LOW LOSS LOW GAIN</b> Blue bar is small negative. Red bar is close to zero or small positive. Green bar is close to zero or small positive.
										The Blue loss of market capitalization recovered by the end of the month. The index did not show much gain.</li><br>
						    	<li><b>LLHG: LOW LOSS HIGH GAIN </b>Blue bar is small negative -- this is compared to all the other blue bars for that year, e..g, the PUSHDOWN cases.</li><br>
						    	<li><b>NON ALIGN</b> Blue bar is LARGE NEGATIVE but green bar is POSITIVE.</li><br>
						    </ul>
